      "start": 13.742,
      "end": 166.578,
      "text": "Narrow\nEmpty tea cups on the table\nLeft a hollow space where we used to sit\nCold\nThe kettle stopped singing\nYour keys stayed on the counter\nI didn't reach for them\nI didn't\nHoly\nKeep it holy\nKeep the body quiet like a grave\nHoly\nKeep it holy\nGiving back the love I never gave\nI never gave\nI never gave\nOoh\nLeft behind\nOoh\nStill on my mind\nDust\nSettling on the Sunday pews\nWood is hard and dry against my spine\nHungry\nI hunger\nI thirst\nI wait\nTethered to a promise that I made\nBefore I knew the weight of midnight\nBefore the salt\nWashed out my eyes\nHoly\nKeep it holy\nKeep the body quiet like a grave\nHoly\nKeep it holy\nGiving back the love I never gave\nI never gave\nI never gave\nOoh\nLeft behind\nOoh\nStill on my mind\nCut the wire\nPut out the fire\nWatch the empire fall apart\nI walk the line\nI waste the time\nI break the heart\nMy own heart\nMy own heart\nMy own heart\nHoly\nKeep it holy\nKeep the body quiet like a grave\nHoly\nKeep it holy\nGiving back the love I never gave\nI never gave\nI never gave\nOne plate\nOne chair\nOne prayer\nAmen\nAmen\nAmen",
